card:
	has styling: false
	notes:
		{{Shuffle back "Nuva" Continuous Spells}}
		{{Place 1 "Nuva" Continuous Spell from your Deck face-up in your Spell & Trap Zone?}}
		{{Negate the effects of 1 other face-up Spell/Trap on the field?}}
		{{Special Summon up to 2 of your banished monsters?}}
		
		Helps your Nuva Symbols dodge removal effects without triggering their drawbacks
		
		Once it has touched six symbols, "unseal the Bahrag" with a generic SS
		=> probably too powerful for that condition though
		
		It would be nice if it could also somehow replace the dodged symbols, but where to find the space for that?
		=> maybe if shuffling back directly does various effects
		=> Problem: Shuffling from GY is necessary to ever have 6 at once and to align with symbol theft mechanics, but the cost of shuffling something from field and shuffling something from GY is way different
		==> case in point: shuffling back a Nuva Symbol on the field to get one from the Deck swaps effects at best, shuffling back one in the GY gives you a fresh Nuva Symbol and goes +1
		==> we could be super cute here and make it "your field or your opponent's GY", so the only way to get 6 symbols is in a mirror match or by using the Nuva Cube alone against a Toa Nuva deck - very lore appropriate
		===> careful - 1+ can only resolve if a Nuva Symbol is in your own deck ... unless it's optional like Wavering Eyes
		===> in general, having mandatory effects that can't always resolve would likely mean you may not freely be able to shuffle back a certain number and thus fail to protect your symbols in some cases, so try to design around that
		====> can be avoided by making it like Kowloon and having all the effects be optional by default, but that means the shuffle must be part of the effect or else it would be possible to "do nothing"
		==> upon further reflection, getting Nuva Symbols into your own GY is generally so bad for you that a way to turn that into a benefit doesn't sound totally unfair, so why not go with "either GY" after all?
		=> Also watch out for Ashable effect components in the optional things, wouldn't want a life-saving shuffle to be negated just because it could theoretically add something to hand
