		Usage A (Lore): Make the Bohrok-Kal impervious to outside harm in "the final moments" before their triumph
		=> implied condition #1: Must be in the said final moments
		==> Timing at start of BP, since Xa-Kal also triggers in battle?
		===> Could also be in your SP if you control a monster that qualifies, since that still means you're about to make your move 
		==> Require banished Bahrag, to have the scene set properly?
		=> implied condition #2: Bohrok-Kal with Krana-Kal, as the Krana-Kal is what turns silver
		=> How far should the protection go? Just effects or also tributing, fusing, etc?
		==> Should Silver Shield itself be SS4?
		=> If Silver Krana-Kal ends up being a monster of its own, that would also need to be involved in this effect somehow
		
		Usage B (Utility): Additional way to attach Krana, in case the OPT on each Bohrok-Kal isn't enough
		=> Also lets you do it without running into monster negates
		
		Which one of these should be the main and which one the GY effect?
		=> Advantage of Lore as GY effect: Not reliant on having the card Set at just the moment when it can actually be used
		==> Since that effect is most likely a trigger effect, this version could also realistically be done as a Spell (Quick-Play or Normal), allowing more immediate access to the utility part
		=> Advantage of Utiltiy as GY effect: Can do it without a turn of setup, which is useful w.r. to the aforementioned avoiding of monster negates
		==> Also would be the proper priority considering the protections from Silver is what the card is about
